JOHANNESBURG - The ANC NEC plans to discuss what’s in the best interests of the country with President Jacob Zuma on Sunday night. That’s according to ANC Chairperson Gwede Mantashe. READ: Everyone's talking Zuma's exit His comments seem to contradict those of the party’s Secretary General Ace Magashule who says it’s an ordinary scheduled meeting of the top six. Mantashe was addressing a church service in Kagiso a short while ago. “We want to ensure stability that’s why tonight we are meeting with president Zuma, we are not going to humiliate him we are going to have a discussion about what is in the best interest fo the country," says Gwede Mantashe, ANC Chairperson.  eNCA